<subSubSection pageId="30" pageNumber="31" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="30.[151,1437,152,642]" pageId="30" pageNumber="31">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[197,322,422,448]" pageId="30" pageNumber="31">Remarks:</emphasis>
Externally 
<taxonomicName box="[463,770,423,448]" class="Insecta" family="Bombyliidae" genus="Hemipenthes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="30" pageNumber="31" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="martinorum">
<emphasis box="[463,770,423,448]" italics="true" pageId="30" pageNumber="31">Hemipenthes martinorum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is similar to 
<taxonomicName box="[929,1053,423,448]" class="Insecta" family="Bombyliidae" genus="Hemipenthes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="30" pageNumber="31" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="wilcoxi">
<emphasis box="[929,1053,423,448]" italics="true" pageId="30" pageNumber="31">H. wilcoxi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
but can be distinguished by the white scales on the fifth and seventh abdominal tergites and the smooth color margin in wing. The smooth color margin and the identical shape of the genitalia relate 
<taxonomicName box="[859,1038,500,525]" class="Insecta" family="Bombyliidae" genus="Hemipenthes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="30" pageNumber="31" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="martinorum">
<emphasis box="[859,1038,500,525]" italics="true" pageId="30" pageNumber="31">H. martinorum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
with 
<emphasis box="[1108,1348,500,525]" italics="true" pageId="30" pageNumber="31">
<taxonomicName box="[1108,1227,500,525]" class="Insecta" family="Bombyliidae" genus="Hemipenthes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="30" pageNumber="31" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="celeris">H. celeris</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName box="[1240,1343,500,525]" class="Insecta" family="Bombyliidae" genus="Hemipenthes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="30" pageNumber="31" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="curta">H. curta</taxonomicName>
,
</emphasis>
and 
<taxonomicName class="Insecta" family="Bombyliidae" genus="Hemipenthes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="30" pageNumber="31" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="pleuralis">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="30" pageNumber="31">H. pleuralis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. This species has an uncommon distribution, as in 
<taxonomicName box="[895,1029,538,563]" class="Insecta" family="Bombyliidae" genus="Hemipenthes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="30" pageNumber="31" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="incisiva">
<emphasis box="[895,1029,538,563]" italics="true" pageId="30" pageNumber="31">H. incisiva</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
it can not be said if this disjunct distribution is real or an effect of the rarity or difficulty to collect this species. Only two specimens from Michoacán, 
<collectingCountry box="[296,385,616,642]" name="Mexico" pageId="30" pageNumber="31">Mexico</collectingCountry>
were available in the revised collections.
</paragraph>
